---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const title = "Policy & disclosures | Soccer 26";
const description = "Soccer 26's disclosures: no affiliate or sportsbook relationships, not betting advice, responsible-gambling resources, data sources & attribution, and a privacy note (no accounts, no tracking).";
const updated = "6 June 2026";
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="pol-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Transparency · The fine print</p>
    <h1>Policy &amp; disclosures</h1>
    <p class="subtle" style="max-width:68ch;margin:0.5rem 0 0;">
      What this site is, what it isn't, where the data comes from, and how it treats your
      privacy. Plain language, no surprises. <span class="pol-upd">Last updated {updated}.</span>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-section">
    <div class="section-head"><h2>No affiliate or sportsbook relationship</h2><span class="rule"></span></div>
    <div class="panel pol-prose">
      <p>Soccer 26 has <b>no affiliate, referral, advertising, or commercial relationship</b>
      with any sportsbook, betting operator, or data reseller. We are not paid if you sign up
      anywhere or place a bet, and there are no tracked outbound betting links. Bookmaker odds
      are displayed <b>solely for comparison and analysis</b> — to measure the model against the
      market and to compute closing-line value. If that ever changes, it will be disclosed here
      and on every page it affects, before the fact.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-section">
    <div class="section-head"><h2>Not betting or financial advice</h2><span class="rule"></span></div>
    <div class="panel pol-prose">
      <p>Everything here is a <b>statistical estimate for interest and education</b>. Model
      probabilities and "edges" are uncertain and frequently wrong; a positive edge is a
      disagreement with the market, not a tip and not a guarantee of profit. Nothing on this site
      is betting, investment, tax, or financial advice, and it is not personalised to you. Any
      decisions you make are your own.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-section">
    <div class="section-head"><h2>Eligibility &amp; jurisdiction</h2><span class="rule"></span></div>
    <div class="panel pol-prose">
      <p>Gambling laws differ by country and region, and many places restrict or prohibit it.
      This is an <b>18+ (or your local legal age)</b> analysis project; it does not target,
      solicit, or knowingly accept users from any jurisdiction where viewing or acting on this
      content is unlawful. <b>It is your responsibility</b> to know and follow the laws that
      apply to you. Gamble only where it is legal, only what you can afford to lose.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-section">
    <div class="section-head"><h2>Responsible gambling</h2><span class="count">help is free</span><span class="rule"></span></div>
    <div class="panel pol-prose">
      <p>Betting should be entertainment, never a way to make money or recover losses. Set time
      and money limits, never chase, and stop if it stops being fun. If gambling is affecting you
      or someone you know, free, confidential help is available:</p>
      <ul class="pol-links">
        <li><a href="https://www.begambleaware.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">BeGambleAware</a> — advice and self-assessment (UK)</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.gamcare.org.uk" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">GamCare</a> — support and the National Gambling Helpline (UK)</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.ncpgambling.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">NCPG</a> — 1-800-GAMBLER (US)</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.gamblersanonymous.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Gamblers Anonymous</a> — peer support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-section">
    <div class="section-head"><h2>Data sources &amp; attribution</h2><span class="rule"></span></div>
    <div class="panel pol-prose">
      <ul class="pol-srcs">
        <li><b>Match odds</b> — <a href="https://the-odds-api.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">The Odds API</a> (consensus &amp; per-book prices for the de-vig, edges, and CLV).</li>
        <li><b>Historical results &amp; team ratings</b> — the public <a href="https://github.com/martj42/international_results" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">martj42 international football results</a> dataset, which trains the Elo ratings.</li>
        <li><b>Team news</b> — public RSS from BBC Sport, The Guardian, and ESPN, shown as headline links back to the source.</li>
        <li><b>Fixtures &amp; venues</b> — the official FIFA World Cup 2026 schedule.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="subtle" style="margin:0.6rem 0 0;">All trademarks and content belong to their
      owners; sources are linked rather than reproduced. How the numbers are produced and audited
      is detailed on the <a href="/methodology">methodology page</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-section">
    <div class="section-head"><h2>Privacy</h2><span class="count">no accounts, no tracking</span><span class="rule"></span></div>
    <div class="panel pol-prose">
      <p>This is a static site with <b>no accounts, no logins, and no analytics or advertising
      trackers</b>. It collects no personal information. Features like your <b>watchlist</b> and
      <b>"Beat the Model" picks</b> are stored only in your own browser's <code>localStorage</code>
      — they never leave your device and are not sent anywhere. The newsletter (when enabled) is
      the only opt-in that would involve a third-party provider, and only with an email you give
      deliberately.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .pol-hero {
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background:
      radial-gradient(120% 140% at 0% 0%, rgba(157,123,255,0.12), transparent 52%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface-2), var(--surface));
    padding: 1.7rem 1.9rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
  }
  .pol-hero h1 { margin: 0.3rem 0 0; }
  .pol-upd { color: var(--muted-2); }
  .mx-section { margin-top: 2rem; }
  .pol-prose { line-height: 1.65; }
  .pol-prose p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); }
  .pol-prose b { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 600; }
  .pol-prose code { font-size: 0.86em; }
  .pol-links, .pol-srcs { margin: 0.7rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8; }
  .pol-srcs b { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 600; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .pol-hero { padding: 1.3rem 1.2rem; } }
</style>
